Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: Advanced Digital Filters

Comprehensive filter design and implementation surpassing SciPy.signal with
classical and modern filter types, adaptive filtering, and optimal design methods.

Features:
- IIR filters (Butterworth, Chebyshev I/II, Elliptic, Bessel)
- FIR filters (Parks-McClellan, windowed design, frequency sampling)
- Adaptive filters (LMS, RLS, Kalman)
- Multirate filters (decimation, interpolation, polyphase)
- Special filters (notch, comb, all-pass, Hilbert transformer)
- Filter banks and wavelets
- Optimal filter design
- Real-time filtering with state management
:End Note

Import "scientific/core/ndarray" as NDArray
Import "scientific/signal/core" as SignalCore
Import "collections" as Collections
Import "math/core" as Math

Type called "IIRFilter":
    filter_type as IIRFilterType
    order as Integer
    cutoff_frequencies as List[Float]
    ripple_db as Optional[Float]
    stopband_attenuation_db as Optional[Float]
    b_coefficients as NDArray.NDArray
    a_coefficients as NDArray.NDArray
    sos_sections as Optional[List[SOSSection]]
    zpk as Optional[ZPKRepresentation]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type IIRFilterType is:
    | Butterworth
    | Chebyshev1
    | Chebyshev2
    | Elliptic
    | Bessel

Type called "SOSSection":
    b0 as Float
    b1 as Float
    b2 as Float
    a0 as Float
    a1 as Float
    a2 as Float

Type called "ZPKRepresentation":
    zeros as NDArray.NDArray
